parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of an accident. Additionally, it can cause electrical accessories such as windshield wipers and headlights to become inoperative, further increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails to return to the running position after starting the engine
the headlights and turn signals do not work
the air conditioning system does not work

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can increase the risk of an accident, as the driver may not be able to alert other drivers or pedestrians of their presence.
The malfunction of the seat heater can cause burns or injuries to the driver or passenger.
symptoms: The seat heater burns a hole through the leather seat cover
causing a hot burning sensation on the driver's leg.

symptoms: or thumping sound when driving over bumps
or when hitting a small bump. The vehicle may experience a slight loss of control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's brakes may not function properly in wet conditions, leading to a delayed or reduced braking response, which can cause accidents or increase the stopping distance, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Long delay before the brakes engage
brakes do not work until held for a few seconds
inability to stop the car within a safe distance

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake noise may be a sign of worn-out brake pads or other brake component failures, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Squeaking or clicking noise when braking.
